WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.800
Hello everyone!

00:04.800 --> 00:10.680
In this video we'll be talking about tiny, tiny RSS.

00:10.680 --> 00:18.800
It is a self-hosted web application that aggregates RSS or atom feeds, allowing users

00:18.800 --> 00:27.480
to subscribe to news, blogs and podcasts and read them in one place with filtering and

00:27.480 --> 00:31.440
tugging.

00:31.440 --> 00:37.580
For the accessing for the first time, we will use the default admin account and default

00:37.580 --> 00:49.800
profile.

00:49.800 --> 00:57.140
Once you are logged in, on the left pane you will find your feed categories and

00:57.140 --> 01:00.620
subscriptions.

01:00.620 --> 01:13.260
The main area displays your articles, which you can quickly toggle between red and red posts.

01:13.260 --> 01:21.980
What actually RSS is, RSS stands for really simple syndication and the current implementation

01:21.980 --> 01:26.380
version of this stack is 2.0.

01:26.380 --> 01:34.060
RSS consists of two components, RSS readers and RSS feeds.

01:34.060 --> 01:38.060
Fits are actually what you will subscribe to.

01:38.060 --> 01:47.060
They are just XML files, a lot of websites have that can be read by the feed reader.

01:47.060 --> 01:58.460
It contains all articles, videos, posts, from source and the readages displays them in

01:58.460 --> 02:02.820
whatever order you choose.

02:02.820 --> 02:10.900
When a website publishes new articles, the feed updates and if you read it gets a new

02:10.900 --> 02:17.780
stuff and displays it for the user.

02:17.780 --> 02:33.740
To add a new feed, just open a website you are interesting in and look for an icon with RSS

02:33.740 --> 02:35.740
feed.

02:35.740 --> 02:42.980
It looks like this.

02:42.980 --> 02:57.900
Copying address of such an icon and in the TTRSS application, click on actions drop down

02:57.900 --> 03:08.860
menu and select subscribe to feed item.

03:08.860 --> 03:22.620
Paste copy link address into URL field and click subscribe button.

03:22.620 --> 03:49.060
Okay, let's add another one feed.

03:49.060 --> 03:57.020
After some time feeds with articles for the last 24 hours will be displayed in folder

03:57.020 --> 04:04.980
uncategorized.

04:04.980 --> 04:12.500
We can organize them into categories and tag them for the fast navigation.

04:12.500 --> 04:18.980
To create a category, click actions drop down menu and select preferences.

04:18.980 --> 04:36.060
Then click on feed stop and then click on categories drop down menu to add category.

04:36.060 --> 04:47.260
Let's add the title tag and click on button.

04:47.260 --> 04:53.580
category was named tag is created.

04:53.580 --> 05:07.220
Let's add another category called news.

05:07.220 --> 05:14.300
We have now two newly added categories.

05:14.300 --> 05:19.980
The assigned feed to a category, we need to drag and drop it into a desired category

05:19.980 --> 05:36.060
folder.

05:36.060 --> 05:44.820
Then click exit preferences.

05:44.820 --> 05:58.580
Now we can see how our feeds located on the specific category folder, news and tag.

05:58.580 --> 06:15.140
We need feed, select feed, click actions and select edit this feed.

06:15.140 --> 06:31.540
We can change any of available fields here, for example feed title.

06:31.540 --> 06:41.580
Then click save button and changes will apply.

06:41.580 --> 06:58.980
While viewing articles, we can mark some of them as start by clicking on star icon.

06:58.980 --> 07:07.700
Same from another feed.

07:07.700 --> 07:28.660
Then they appear in start articles folder.

07:28.660 --> 07:45.060
Moving through the articles, they become red automatically.

07:45.060 --> 07:54.420
We can also mark item as red or unread for simply.

07:54.420 --> 08:09.860
Select desired articles and choose under adoption from filtering drop down menu.

08:09.860 --> 08:20.740
The article selected and let's make it under red.

08:20.740 --> 08:25.500
Click on the article appear to be unread.

08:25.500 --> 08:41.260
To remove feed, select feed, click on right mouse button and select edit feed from drop

08:41.260 --> 08:47.260
down context menu.

08:47.260 --> 08:51.580
Click in alert window.

08:51.580 --> 08:59.260
The feed will be removed with all its content.

08:59.260 --> 09:06.580
TTRSS application uses background process to update feeds automatically.

09:06.580 --> 09:09.380
Add regular intervals.

09:09.420 --> 09:15.140
Typically it's a Chrome job or diamond.

09:15.140 --> 09:25.300
By default this interval is set to set in minutes but can be changed.

09:25.380 --> 09:33.060
Now let's change it to 15 minutes.

09:33.060 --> 09:42.300
After changes, click save configuration.

09:42.300 --> 09:49.300
attering mouse pointer on a feed.

09:49.300 --> 09:58.500
We can see a time of the last feed update.

09:58.500 --> 10:15.900
We can also force feed update by clicking on feed title.

10:15.900 --> 10:23.540
All articles from all feeds are collected in all articles folder.

10:23.540 --> 10:30.100
For the fastest search of articles we can use tags.

10:30.100 --> 10:42.300
Some articles might already have tags.

10:42.300 --> 10:53.140
And some of them do not have any tags.

10:53.140 --> 11:09.060
Click on plus sign button and add tags separated by commas.

11:09.060 --> 11:14.180
Click save button.

11:14.180 --> 11:44.140
We can then select articles which should be displayed by clicking on tag name.

11:44.420 --> 12:06.420
We can also use select by tag option from actions menu.

12:06.420 --> 12:19.820
For example I selected Linux kernel keyword and I can see an article which contains Linux

12:19.820 --> 12:26.180
kernel.

12:26.180 --> 12:32.420
We can also create filters to out-to-tag articles.

12:32.460 --> 12:44.060
For example create filter to tag all articles with Google as tag.

12:44.060 --> 12:55.300
Go to preferences, click on filters, top, create filter.

12:55.300 --> 13:14.620
Let's create filter with caption.

13:14.620 --> 13:42.260
Add new rule and apply action.

13:42.260 --> 13:49.260
This is tested.

13:49.260 --> 13:55.940
We can see that two articles are caged and clicked.

13:55.940 --> 14:01.700
One filter is created.

14:01.700 --> 14:10.180
Exit preferences.

14:10.180 --> 14:23.060
We can also create filters to out-to-mark articles as read or out-to-delete based on keywords.

14:23.060 --> 14:28.540
We can host the TRS application for multiple users.

14:28.540 --> 14:37.380
Each with their own feed list, preferences and filters.

14:37.380 --> 14:53.300
In actions preferences, choose top users and create new user.

15:07.380 --> 15:22.340
And try to login with another user.

15:37.380 --> 16:01.140
Log out and login as admin.

16:01.140 --> 16:10.380
If we need to migrate feeds from another reader or back-the-map, then you can access support

16:10.380 --> 16:26.460
a HTML, import and export.

16:26.460 --> 16:36.620
Opemail files are a universal format supported by nearly every RSS reader.

16:36.620 --> 16:40.300
Steps for export.

16:40.300 --> 16:50.540
Go to preferences, click on feed, top, click export, opemail.

16:50.540 --> 17:05.180
Save opemail file locally.

17:05.180 --> 17:31.900
To import opemail, click import my opemail file by choosing first.

17:31.900 --> 17:52.940
And everything has imported.

17:52.940 --> 18:03.100
Exit preferences.

18:03.100 --> 18:14.340
So tiny tiny RSS is written in PHP and works with Postgres or MySQL database.

18:14.340 --> 18:24.100
You can deploy it on any Linux based server manually or using Docker.

18:24.100 --> 18:43.100
In my case, application is running as Docker container.

18:43.100 --> 18:48.140
Installation of TTRSS application is quite easy.

18:48.140 --> 19:11.820
This is the clone of GitHub master branch and run Docker ComposeUpCommand.

19:18.140 --> 19:44.500
OK, let's install it from scratch.

19:48.140 --> 20:02.720
Then copy copemil.

20:03.000 --> 20:06.640
And add darker

20:09.040 --> 20:10.800
一部分

20:32.720 --> 20:56.720
It will take for a while.

20:56.720 --> 21:06.720
It will take for a while.

21:27.720 --> 21:41.720
Now application is up and running.

21:41.720 --> 21:47.720
Yep.

21:47.720 --> 21:51.720
And then, did it.

21:51.720 --> 21:57.720
Thanks for attention.

